claim((uint256,uint256),address,uint256,.notice: Claim back stake. If only losing an auction, the same amount initially staked          will be sent back. If losing an auction while being a validator, the amount sent back = stake + rewards - penalties, as determined by the CFE

params.amount: The amount of stake to be locked up
params.sigData: The keccak256 hash over the msg (uint) (which is the calldata                  for this function with empty msgHash and sig) and sig over that hash                  from the current governance key (uint)
params.staker: The staker who is to be sent FLIP

getAuctionEndBlock().notice: Get the end block of the latest auction. Auctions are valid          up until, and including, this block number

returns._0: The block number that ends this auction, inclusive (uint)

getEmissionPerSec().notice: Get the emission rate of FLIP in seconds

getKeyManager().notice: Get the KeyManager address/interface that's used to validate sigs

getLastClaimTime().notice: Get the last time that claim() was called, in unix time

returns._0: The time of the last claim (uint)

getMinimumStake().notice: Get the minimum amount of stake that's required for a bid          attempt in the auction to be valid - used to prevent sybil attacks

getTotalStaked().notice: Get the total amount of FLIP currently staked by all stakers, used          to always ensure collateralisation

returns._0: The current total of stake in this contract (uint)
